cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.LG 

This paper deals with the problem of power allocation in cognitive femtocell networks, which is a subfield of wireless networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a distributed reinforcement learning technique, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with information theory (cs.IT) as it discusses the capacity levels of the femtocells and macrocells. The paper proposes a cooperative approach for the distributed learning algorithm, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses simulation results to evaluate the performance of the proposed algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
